column48: SRS Vasu Bedi with SOs Sor, Mark & Kulwinder.

Procedural Error: During the nightly Card Pick up process, Security Officer Priyank Garg failed to inform Surveillance that he will be entering the Card Rec room with the number of RJ. This is contrary to OPPM & General Orders 2024, Page 33 "Lock the Card Rec Cart and return it to Card Rec with the Table Games Supervisor • “Sky copy, entering Card Rec with the Cart” before opening door.".  Security Relief Supervisor Vasu Bedi was informed and Security Manager James Taylor was informed via email.
Fire drill was initiated at 07:13. Stage 2 set at 07:19. Simulated fire in the green room. Scans were done.

Surveillance Initiated Review: During a camera check, Surveillance noted a male loitering in the stairwell near the pedway. Upon review, the male appeared to have been in the stairwell for approximately 40 minutes, occasionally tinkering with items on the wall mounted heater. Security Relief Supervisor Darcy Cross was informed, and he proceeded to the area and spoke with the man. He left property on foot after a few minutes.
Rezza Tafreshi (Northeastern) - addressing green room access issues

Requested Observation: Security Manager James Taylor and Security Relief Supervisor Darcy Cross advised they'd be speaking with an unknown female and male, found sleeping in the parkade elevator stairwell. Due to the location of the individuals, they were unable to be observed on camera at that time. According to SRS Darcy, the pair were asleep on a couple of trash bins in the stairwell on level 7. Live coverage was initiated as the pair made their way off property, one via the pedway, and the other on foot towards the downtown area. SRS Darcy also wished to know when they arrived in the stairwell, and with a review it was determined they did so at 0320hrs. He was informed and stated that nothing additional was required.
Observation of Count Room Attendant Rose Harding opening/processing Table Games.

Requested Review: SRS Darcy Cross contacted Surveillance to request a review of a maroon 4-door car on Parkade level 5 Up. SM James Taylor wished to know when it had arrived and who it belonged to. Upon review, the vehicle in question arrived shortly after 08:00, and was driven by Banquets Manager Megan Lewis. Darcy was informed.

Surveillance Initiated Review: HRP advised that a female, identified as Cennie Rawding, reported believing her drink had been spiked while she was in the casino on the night of 7 February 2026. HRP provided only her name and a photograph, with no additional details such as time of visit, clothing description, companions, or exact location within the property. Using the provided image, Surveillance initiated a review of all relevant camera coverage for that night, including Post‑1, Post‑2, and the 3Sixty bar area. Surveillance was unable to locate the female due to limited information and the review remains inconclusive. Picture/Subject saved as "Rawding, Cennie".

Requested Review: Floor Supervisor Tim Moffatt requested a review of the last spin on RL1 when 10B hit.  Tim stated that Dealer Barbara MacDonald had marked 7R in error and he wanted to know the relevant wagers,  Upon review, it appeared that the player using brick coloured non-value chips had a straight up and a split wager and the 2 players playing brown and yellow non-value chips each had straight up wagers.  All wagers appeared to be one chip.  Tim was advised of the findings.

Procedural Error: As the result of a review, Surveillance noted a procedural error when  Floor Supervisor Tim Moffatt advised that Dealer Barbara MacDonald marked the wrong number in error on RL1 and wanted to know if there were any winning wagers on 10B.  Upon review, Barbara marked 7R in error and cleared what appeared to be 1 brick, 1 brown, and 1 yellow non-value chips straight up on 10B and left one brick 7/10 split wager on the board. Tim was advised of the findings.  Gaming Manager Tom Sneddon was advised via email. Copied to DE2026-13.
